<body><p>GE.10-14329 
</p>
<p><b>Human Rights Council 
Fourteenth session 
</b>Agenda item 3 
<b>Promotion and protection of all human rights, civil, 
political, economic, social and cultural rights,  
including the right to development 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Pakistan (on behalf of the Organization of the Islamic Conference): amendments to 
draft resolution A/HRC/14/L.5 
</b></p>
<p><b> 1. The second preambular paragraph <i>should read</i> 
</b></p>
<p> <i>Recalling also</i> articles 18, 19 and 20 of the International Covenant on Civil and 
Political Rights, article 18 of the Universal Declaration of Human Rights, article 2, 
paragraph 2 of the International Covenant on Economic, Social and Cultural Rights, articles 
4 and 5 of the International Convention on the Elimination of All Forms of Racial 
Discrimination and other relevant human rights provisions, 
</p>
<p><b> 2. Paragraph 3 <i>should read</i> 
</b></p>
<p> <i>Decides</i> to extend the mandate of the Special Rapporteur for a further period of three 
years and, in this context, invites the Special Rapporteur, in accordance with the mandate 
specified in Council resolution 6/37, inter alia:  
</p>
<p> <i>(a)</i> To examine incidents of incitement to religious hatred, discrimination, 
intolerance and violence, manifested in particular by derogatory stereotyping and profiling, 
as well as by stigmatization of persons based on their religion or belief, whether involving 
the use of print, audio-visual or electronic media or any other means, and to recommend 
appropriate remedial measures; 
</p>
<p> <i>(b)</i> To encourage the adoption of measures and policies at the national, regional 
and international levels that ensure respect for places of worship, religious sites and public 
expressions of spiritual and religious beliefs, as these have more than material significance 
for the dignity and lives of members of communities holding these beliefs, thereby ensuring 
that their right to manifest their religion or belief in practice, worship, teaching and 
observance is protected and that there is no hindrance to the full enjoyment of their right to 
freedom of religion and conscience; 
</p>
<p> <i>(c)</i> To report on instances/acts, both in law and practice, that constitute 
violations of the fundamental right to freedom of religion or belief, taking into account 
articles 18, 19 and 20 of the International Covenant on Civil and Political Rights;  
</p>
<p> <i>(d)</i> To work closely with mass media organizations to ensure that they create and 
promote an atmosphere of respect and tolerance for religious and cultural diversity, as well 
as for multiculturalism; 
</p>

<p><b> 3. Paragraph 6 <i>should read</i> 
</b></p>
<p> <i>Requests</i> the Special Rapporteur to submit her/his reports to the Council in 
accordance with its annual programme of work, and the next annual report in 2011, which 
should focus on, inter alia, the implementation of paragraph 3 of the present resolution and 
to make recommendations thereon; 
</p>
<p>    </p>

